Date:5/16/2007 12:13:10 PM
From:MCsweet

Madharry,

Yes, I guess all those jokes about Canada being the 51st state really irks
Canadian regulators. Seriously, I think they would much prefer to see US
investors not invest in Canada. US investors often can't participate in special
corporate actions (rights offerings, dividend reinvest, etc) and sometimes are
restricted from having too large a % ownership of a security. Regulators
probably are interested in protecting US shareholders who they don't want
anyway.

MC
