Edit - News snip today from Istanbul publication:

Ak&#231;akoca gas will meet one-tenth of consumption

The natural gas extracted in Ak&#231;akoca will meet one-tenth of the gas
consumed in Turkey, Energy Minister Hilmi G&#252;ler has said. 

Speaking at a ceremony marking the integration of the gas to the domestic
distribution network yesterday, G&#252;ler said they had conducted long-term
research before beginning to drill. He also said he had monitored Norway's
search for gas, which found deposits on the 33rd drill, but said Turkish
engineers had found gas on their first drill. "I hope we will become a country
that extracts, refines and consumes its own oil and gas," he said.

G&#252;ler said 2 million cubic meters of natural gas would be produced in
Ak&#231;akoca, adding that the amount was equal to the total consumption of
Samsun, Sivas, Erzurum, Malatya, Kayseri, &#199;orum, Konya, D&#252;zce and
Aksaray put together. He said a new natural gas depot with a capacity to store
1.6 billion cubic meters would also be built in Silivri.

G&#252;ler said with Baku-Tbilisi-Ceyhan oil pipeline, the Shahdeniz and Blue
Stream natural gas pipeline, Turkey had become a hub and that with these new
projects they also wanted to be an oil and gas-producing country.

The gas well was drilled by a joint initiative between the state-owned Turkish
Petroleum Corporation (TPAO), US-based Toreador and Stratic Enerji, according
to the Anatolia news agency. The gas reserves in Ak&#231;akoca are larger than
the combined TPAO gas reserves in the Thrace region. The search for gas was
launched in 2004 and two platforms, Prometeu and Saturn, drilled 13 wells
varying in depth from 640 meters to 980 meters. Nine were prepared for
production, three were closed because of poor yields and one was dry. Two
million cubic meters gas of is expected to be extracted per day from the nine
wells.

21.05.2007

Today's Zaman Istanbul

